@startuml

title MCP + OpenWebUI + OAuth Architecture

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

actor User

package "Internal Network (192.168.2.0/24)" {

  node "Open WebUI\n192.168.2.15:8080" as OPENWEB

  node "vLLM Server\nLocal LLM" as VLLM

  node "NGINX Reverse Proxy\n192.168.2.15:443" as NGINX
}

package "Service Network (10.10.10.0/24)" {

  node "MS-365 MCP Server\n10.10.10.104:3000" as MCP
}

cloud "Microsoft Entra ID" as ENTRA

cloud "Microsoft Graph API" as GRAPH

User --> OPENWEB : HTTPS Chat

OPENWEB --> VLLM : Prompt + Tool Calling

VLLM --> OPENWEB : Tool Request

OPENWEB --> NGINX : HTTPS /mcp

NGINX --> MCP : HTTP proxy_pass

MCP --> User : OAuth Redirect

User --> ENTRA : Login + MFA

ENTRA --> User : OAuth Callback

User --> OPENWEB : OAuth Response

OPENWEB --> NGINX : Authenticated MCP Calls

NGINX --> MCP : MCP Requests

MCP --> GRAPH : Graph API Calls

GRAPH --> MCP : Mail / Calendar Data

MCP --> OPENWEB : Tool Results

OPENWEB --> VLLM : Context Injection

VLLM --> OPENWEB : Final Response

OPENWEB --> User : Chat Response

note right of MCP
Internal MCP server
Streamable HTTP
Scoped permissions
end note

note bottom of VLLM
Local inference only
No external LLM APIs
end note

@enduml
